Georgia massacre: Activists reframe racist lynching in hope of justice
A Ford Mercury-branded car passes a crowd in the small town of Monroe in the Georgian countryside and continues its journey towards the small bridge of Moore’s Ford.
The car has four black passengers and a white driver. Four armed men block the road before the car reaches the bridge.
The leader of the group, a middle-aged man dressed in a striped suit, takes a deep breath from his cigar and looks through the windshield.
The passengers are scared.
