The Spanish league blocked the move earlier on Thursday when it rejected the first payment attempt by Neymar's representatives.
According to the rules of the league, a buying club cannot pay the purchase price directly to the seller, but the player must buy out his own contract, which is done by recycling the money through the league.
In practice, PSG has paid the amount to Neymar and his representatives, who delivered the money through the league to Barcelona.
